<S ID='S-47' AZ='OWN'> From this representation , we can derive a formula describing its length in bits . </S>
<S ID='S-48' AZ='OWN'> However , the discrete form of the formula would not work well in practice for our simulations . </S>
<S ID='S-49' AZ='OWN'> Instead , we use a continuous approximation of the discrete formula ; this approximation typically involves dropping the ceiling function from length computations . </S>
<S ID='S-50' AZ='OWN'> For example , we sometimes use a self-delimiting representation for integers ( as described in <REFAUTHOR>Li and Vitnyi</REFAUTHOR> , pp. 74 - 75 ) . </S>
