<HEADER ID='H-4'> Phonotactics </HEADER>
<P>
<S ID='S-97' AZ='OWN'> Phonotactic knowledge was given to the system as a list of licit initial and final consonant clusters of English words ; this list was checked against all six samples so that the list was maximally permissive ( e.g. , the underlined consonant cluster in explore could be divided as ek-splore or eks-plore ) . </S>
<S ID='S-98' AZ='OWN'> In those simulations which used the phonotactic knowledge , a word boundary could not be inserted when doing so would create a word initial or final consonant cluster not on the list or would create a word without a vowel . </S>
